<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>TSI 07-12-02 - Rubber Vibration Damper Replacement Kits</stitle>
    <tsi id="tSI071202" year="2007" tsitype="engine">
        <tsinumber>07-12-02</tsinumber>
        <replace>
            <tsinumber>TSI-06-12-26</tsinumber>
        </replace>
        <tsidate>February 2007</tsidate>
        <subjectfile>Engine</subjectfile>
        <subjectgroup>
            <subject>Rubber Vibration Damper Replacement Kits</subject>
        </subjectgroup>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <engfamgroup/>

                <engfam>DT 570
                    <snrange>2000001 through 2999999</snrange>
                </engfam>
                <engfam>HT 570
                    <snrange>2000001 through 2999999</snrange>
                </engfam>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>Three new rubber vibration damper replacement kits have been released to eliminate premature belt
                    wear. Starting on 11/03/2006, the DT 570 and HT 570 diesel engines went into production with a
                    smaller rubber vibration damper. This is the same vibration damper found in the three replacement
                    kits. This damper is usable on all DT 570 and HT 570 diesel engines, including those manufactured
                    with the larger viscous vibration damper. Use the service kit and drive belt specified in the
                    following tables for the vehicle / engine application.
                </para>
                <para>Labels are provided in the kit. These labels alert the owner or mechanic that the vehicle has a
                    different drive belt. The label also indicates that the vibration damper, water pump, and fan pulley
                    have been upgraded.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <caution>
                        <para>To prevent engine damage, use correct replacement kit and belt specified for the
                            vehicle.
                        </para>
                    </caution>
                </specpara>
                <para>For Horton Drivemaster Applications; determine which kit to order by removing the drive belt and
                    using a tape measure to measure the distance around the fan pulley. This measurement will determine
                    which Horton ratio kit to order.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>When measuring the fan pulley size, place the tape measure around the center ribs of the
                            pulley. Do not place the tape measure around the outer most flanges of the pulley.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>Use the Horton 1.2:1 ratio kit (1875872C91) if the measurement is approximately 686mm (27
                            inches) in length.
                        </para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Use the Horton 1.3:1 ratio kit (1875871C91) if the measurement is approximately 610mm (24
                            inches) in length.
                        </para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
